  "text": "Since each eddy is spatially bounded, the velocity field corresponding to each eddy will inevitably be negligible at a sufficient distance from the location of the eddy, and this distance is proportional to the height of the eddy. Using this, [CITATION_1] showed that the log-law for the flow profile follows from Campbell's theorem.",
